th-birthday-cut-through-hollywood-glamour-to-reveal-the-stars-human-side-180988726/</guid></item><item><title>微塑料在大气中盘旋，它们可能会导致气候变化</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/microplastics-are-swirling-around-in-the-atmosphere-where-they-might-be-contributing-to-climate-change-180988704/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，空气中的塑料颗粒，尤其是彩色颗粒，吸收的阳光多于反射的阳光，从而加热周围的空气</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 16:49:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/microplastics-are-swirling-around-in-the-atmosphere-where-they-might-be-contributing-to-climate-change-180988704/</guid></item><item><title>本杰明·富兰克林在这枚他委托纪念独立战争中的美国和法国盟友的奖章中设计了自由女神像</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/benjamin-franklin-styled-lady-libertys-look-in-this-medal-he-commissioned-to-honor-american-and-french-allies-in-the-revolutionary-war-180988723/</link><description>富兰克林将艺术与外交结合起来，创造了美国自由主义。为纪念美国成立 250 周年，巴黎造币厂对设计进行了更新</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 16:03:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/benjamin-franklin-styled-lady-libertys-look-in-this-medal-he-commissioned-to-honor-american-and-french-allies-in-the-revolutionary-war-180988723/</guid></item><item><title>英国国王铸造这些硬币是为了抵御维京人的入侵。相反，航海袭击者将便士变成了珠宝</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-english-king-minted-these-coins-to-ward-off-a-viking-invasion-instead-the-seafaring-raiders-turned-the-pennies-into-jewelry-180988716/</link><description>不准备者埃塞尔雷德将对其王国的攻击视为神圣的报应。他希望公开忏悔的表现，包括制作带有宗教图像的硬币，将有助于赢得上帝的宽恕</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 11:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-english-king-minted-these-coins-to-ward-off-a-viking-invasion-instead-the-seafaring-raiders-turned-the-pennies-into-jewelry-180988716/</guid></item><item><title>新线索有助于解开一位英国著名艺术家肖像画中被奴役男孩的谜团</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-clues-help-solve-the-mystery-of-an-enslaved-boy-pictured-in-a-portrait-by-a-leading-english-artist-180988717/</link><description>约书亚·雷诺兹 (Joshua Reynolds) 创作的一幅油画描绘了一名海军军官和一名黑人儿童，直到研究人员搜索了船长的日志、信件和海军部记录后，他们的生活故事才被知晓。</description><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 21:57:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-clues-help-solve-the-mystery-of-an-enslaved-boy-pictured-in-a-portrait-by-a-leading-english-artist-180988717/</guid></item><item><title>这些唱歌的老鼠来回吱吱叫，而且不会中断。科学家发现了他们令人印象深刻的歌曲背后的大脑通路</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-singing-mice-squeak-back-and-forth-and-dont-interrupt-scientists-found-the-brain-pathway-behind-their-impressive-songs-180988720/</link><description>阿尔斯通的唱歌小鼠可以发出复杂​​的声音，甚至可以互相礼貌地交谈。使这成为可能的神经回路比研究人员预期的要简单</description><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 20:44:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-singing-mice-squeak-back-and-forth-and-dont-interrupt-scientists-found-the-brain-pathway-behind-their-impressive-songs-180988720/</guid></item><item><title>研究人员在令人惊叹的苏格兰公园发现了秘密非法威士忌酿酒厂的遗迹</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/researchers-discovered-the-remnants-of-a-secret-illegal-distillery-in-a-stunning-scottish-park-180988718/</link><description>几个世纪前苏格兰宣布无证蒸馏为非法后，铜制蒸馏器可能被用来酿造威士忌，因此被隐藏起来，远离税务人员的监督</description><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 20:23:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/researchers-discovered-the-remnants-of-a-secret-illegal-distillery-in-a-stunning-scottish-park-180988718/</guid></item><item><title>澳大利亚著名的十二使徒岩地标花了数百万年才从海中升起</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/australias-famous-twelve-apostles-landmark-rose-out-of-the-sea-across-missions-of-years-180988715/</link><description>这个标志性的旅游目的地提供了美丽的景色，同时也代表了地球气候历史的实物记录</description><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 18:52:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/australias-famous-twelve-apostles-landmark-rose-out-of-the-sea-across-missions-of-years-180988715/</guid></item><item><title>1969 年，披头士乐队进行了最后一场演出。他们在伦敦的临时屋顶舞台很快将成为博物馆</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-1969-the-beatles-played-one-final-show-their-makeshift-rooftop-stage-in-london-will-soon-become-a-museum-180988714/</link><description>来到萨维尔街 3 号的游客将能够看到重建的地下录音室，披头士乐队在那里制作了他们的最后一张专辑《Let It Be》，并站在屋顶上，乐队在那里为伦敦人带来了一场惊喜的音乐会</description><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 18:40:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-1969-the-beatles-played-one-final-show-their-makeshift-rooftop-stage-in-london-will-soon-become-a-museum-180988714/</guid></item><item><title>查看赢得德国自然摄影协会年度竞赛的 15 张令人惊叹的照片</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-15-stunning-images-that-won-the-german-society-for-nature-photographys-annual-contest-180988711/</link><description>从猛冲的青蛙到企鹅的雄伟动作，这些获奖照片捕捉到了野生动物的奇迹和自然景观的美丽</description><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 14:42:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-15-stunning-images-that-won-the-german-society-for-nature-photographys-annual-contest-180988711/</guid></item><item><title>美国宇航局好奇号火星车的手臂上卡了一块火星岩石好几天。看着它最终把顽固的石头抖掉</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasas-curiosity-rover-had-a-martian-rock-stuck-on-its-arm-for-days-watch-it-successfully-shook-the-stubborn-stone-off-180988708/</link><description>据航天局称，虽然钻探使岩石破裂，但这是该仪器第一次意外地从地面拉出整块岩石</description><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasas-curiosity-rover-had-a-martian-rock-stuck-on-its-arm-for-days-watch-it-successfully-shook-the-stubborn-stone-off-180988708/</guid></item><item><title>为什么这位富有的苏格兰人在数百年前付钱给珠宝商用金线包裹他的牙齿？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-did-this-wealthy-scotsman-pay-a-jeweler-to-wrap-his-teeth-in-gold-wire-hundreds-of-years-ago-180988709/</link><description>牙桥的早期例子揭示了中世纪晚期和现代早期世界的健康、财富和社会价值观</description><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026