ps://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-franklin-expedition-officer-died-in-the-arctic-in-uniform-that-didnt-belong-to-him-now-dna-has-revealed-his-identity-180988702/</link><description>新研究确定了 1845 年西北航道搜寻行动中的四名成员的身份，其中包括一个长期以来令历史学家迷惑不解的纸质钱包的主人</description><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 16:07:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-franklin-expedition-officer-died-in-the-arctic-in-uniform-that-didnt-belong-to-him-now-dna-has-revealed-his-identity-180988702/</guid></item><item><title>一项新的遗传学研究表明，罗马帝国的衰落与其说是一场文明的冲突，不如说是一次融合的机会</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-fall-of-the-roman-empire-was-less-a-clash-of-civilizations-and-more-an-opportunity-to-mix-and-mingle-a-new-genetics-study-shows-180988699/</link><description>研究人员分析了现代德国中世纪早期坟墓的基因组，推测前罗马帝国的人们在帝国灭亡后不久就与日耳曼人组成了家庭</description><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 15:54:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-fall-of-the-roman-empire-was-less-a-clash-of-civilizations-and-more-an-opportunity-to-mix-and-mingle-a-new-genetics-study-shows-180988699/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，野生凤头鹦鹉通过模仿朋友来了解哪些零食可以安全食用</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/wild-cockatoos-learn-which-snacks-are-safe-to-eat-by-copying-their-friends-new-research-suggests-180988696/</link><description>咀嚼错误的食物可能会导致疾病，但社会学习可能有助于鸟类避免犯下潜在的致命错误。这种现象可能有助于解释为什么某些凤头鹦鹉在城市环境中表现得如此出色</description><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 15:44:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/wild-cockatoos-learn-which-snacks-are-safe-to-eat-by-copying-their-friends-new-research-suggests-180988696/</guid></item></channel></rss>